    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-03-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-03-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="579"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d579">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Señor <persName
                            type="to">Polo de Bernabé</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-03-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 30, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge
                    receipt of your note of the 28th instant, referring to our recent conversations,
                        <pb facs="0821" n="725" xml:id="pg_725"/> and informing me that His
                    Majesty’s Government would not object to the sending of supplies to Cuba for the
                    reconcentrados, the amount of same to be appropriated by the Congress of the
                    United States, provided that there would be no change whatever in the existing
                    arrangements respecting conveyance and distribution of such supplies.</p>
                <p>Thanking you for your prompt action and interest in this humanitarian
                    undertaking, I remain, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William R. Day</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Assistant
                            Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
